=== Root-cause observation for Clause 6 failure ===
CodeMirror 6's `bracketMatching()` extension highlights matching brackets with the class `cm-matchingBracket`, NOT `.cm-bracket-match`. After injecting `()` and placing the cursor inside:
  - element `.cm-matchingBracket` exists
  - computed style shows: outline: rgb(224, 224, 224), border-color: rgb(224, 224, 224)
The built styles.css (both targets) contains rules for `.cm-bracket-match` (light + dark) but those rules never target a real DOM class, so the custom background/outlines are dead CSS.

